displayHelp() - Static method in class com.cafebabe.core.Menu
 
DIV - Class in com.cafebabe.core.instructions
DIV is the representation of the meta instruction that relate to the division of two entities, this meta instruction include the following bytecode instructions {ddiv, fdiv, idiv, ldiv} This representation contains information about the bytecode instruction and its context, those information are an InstructionHandle object(BCEL) that contain also information about the instruction as the name), the number of registers used by the method in which this instruction is located, the topStack value of the method at the time this instruction is executed, the number of instruction present in the method were this instruction take place, the number of the instruction in the instructions list of the instruction's method, the method name of the instruction's method, the name of the instruction's class.
DIV(InstructionHandle, short, short, int, int, int, String, String, String) - Constructor for class com.cafebabe.core.instructions.DIV
Constructor of the DIV representation
DUP - Class in com.cafebabe.core.instructions
DUP is the representation of the meta instruction that relate to the duplication of the value at the top of the operand stack, this meta instruction include the following bytecode instructions {dup, dup_x1, dup_x2} This representation contains information about the bytecode instruction and its context, those information are an InstructionHandle object(BCEL) that contain also information about the instruction as the name), the number of registers used by the method in which this instruction is located, the topStack value of the method at the time this instruction is executed, the number of instruction present in the method were this instruction take place, the number of the instruction in the instructions list of the instruction's method, the method name of the instruction's method, the name of the instruction's class.

Constructor of the DUP representation
